          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1725535590162-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, remove from the heat and add your<strong> bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the grains are completely coated</p><p>Add 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the bulgur wheat has cooked – this is your <strong>tomatoey bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1725535594744-x200.jpg",
